seems odd. I'm wondering if this satisfies dynamic access. If we reach the call site successfully, could the agent record the target as `java.lang.String`? I think I could create a test class, `CustomClassLoader`, that extends `ClassLoader` and overrides `loadClass(String name)`. If the name is `org.example.ContextDriver`, it returns `String.class`. Otherwise, it throws a `ClassNotFoundException`.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering testing paths**\\n\\nI'm thinking about writing robust tests with three explicit paths, and I’m wondering if I should avoid using the JUnit assertThrows closure. Maybe I should go for try/catch along with a boolean to ensure everything works under Native Image. But then I’m concerned that a failed reflection won't get recorded, so I'll need to use an actual successful call like Class.forName(\\\"java.lang.String\\\") for line 702. It’s a bit tricky, but I’ll figure it out!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining test integration**\\n\\nI'm looking at build.gradle to check if it includes all test classes for native tests. The dynamic agent generates metadata, but initially, the Java run might act differently for native tests, especially if there's no nested test metadata. The TCK agent does collect data, but I'm unsure if I should add a dependency. I could potentially use the existing JDK driver, although Derby isn't included in it. I'm thinking of creating a public static inner class, DummyDriver, for the SQL driver implementation. I'll also need to ensure methods are properly implemented, including getting a version-agnostic name for the driver.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class loading issues**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how Class.forName uses the Sql class loader with the parent app that contains H2, which is fine as long as the dependency is present. If I don’t add the dependency, that won't work, and downloading it isn’t ideal. I wonder if I could use module/platform classes that are visible to bootstrap. In that case, Class.forName would succeed, but I would need a custom loader for the context.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_mMRKjBbLZDnCTOppt6bXk9Ec|fc_0163840d26182cc3016a27435376b081978283453aeb35f8cf", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.codehaus.groovy/groovy-all/2.3.6/src/test/groovy/org_codehaus_groovy/groovy_all/SqlTest.groovy", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_codehaus_groovy.groovy_all\n\nimport groovy.sql.Sql\nimport groovy.transform.CompileStatic\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n\nimport java.sql.Connection\nimport java.sql.Driver\nimport java.sql.DriverPropertyInfo\nimport java.sql.SQLException\nimport java.sql.SQLFeatureNotSupportedException\nimport java.util.logging.Logger\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertThrows\n\npublic class SqlTest {\n    @Test\n    @CompileStatic\n    void loadsDriverClassVisibleToSqlClassLoader() {\n        Sql.loadDriver(VisibleDriver.name)\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    @CompileStatic\n    void loadsDriverClassFromThreadContextClassLoader() {\n        ClassLoader originalContextClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader()\n        ContextOnlyDriverClassLoader contextClassLoader = new ContextOnlyDriverClassLoader(VisibleDriver)\n\n        try {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(contextClassLoader)\n            Sql.loadDriver(ContextOnlyDriverClassLoader.CONTEXT_DRIVER_NAME)\n        } finally {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalContextClassLoader)\n        }\n\n        assertThat(contextClassLoader.requestedNames).containsExactly(\n                ContextOnlyDriverClassLoader.CONTEXT_DRIVER_NAME)\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    @CompileStatic\n    void reportsClassNotFoundWhenDriverCannotBeResolved() {\n        ClassLoader originalContextClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader()\n\n        try {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(new RejectingClassLoader())\n            assertThrows(ClassNotFoundException) {\n                Sql.loadDriver('org.example.jdbc.MissingDriver')\n            }\n        } finally {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalContextClassLoader)\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class ContextOnlyDriverClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        public static final String CONTEXT_DRIVER_NAME = 'org.example.jdbc.ContextOnlyDriver'\n\n        private final Class<?> driverClass\n        public final List<String> requestedNames = []\n\n        ContextOnlyDriverClassLoader(Class<?> driverClass) {\n            super(null)\n            this.driverClass = driverClass\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        Class<?> loadClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            requestedNames.add(name)\n            if (CONTEXT_DRIVER_NAME == name) {\n                return driverClass\n            }\n            throw new ClassNotFoundException(name)\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class RejectingClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        RejectingClassLoader() {\n            super(null)\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        Class<?> loadClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            throw new ClassNotFoundException(name)\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class VisibleDriver implements Driver {\n        @Override\n        Connection connect(String url, Properties info) throws SQLException {\n            return null\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        boolean acceptsURL(String url) throws SQLException {\n            return false\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        DriverPropertyInfo[] getPropertyInfo(String url, Properties info) throws SQLException {\n            return new DriverPropertyInfo[0]\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        int getMajorVersion() {\n            return 1\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        int getMinorVersion() {\n            return 0\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        boolean jdbcCompliant() {\n            return false\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        Logger getParentLogger() throws SQLFeatureNotSupportedException {\n            return Logger.getLogger(VisibleDriver.name)\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 12262, "output": 3860, "cacheRead": 11776, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27898, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780957956144, "responseId": "resp_0163840d26182cc3016a2743052f648197af355f6f7a657255"}}
