 target. If the caller is Class.forName, I should throw an exception, but if it’s from Sql.loadDriver at line 711, I could return the VisibleDriver instead. For loading Sql itself, I might delegate much to the parent class, except when it comes to groovy.sql.Sql. But here’s the catch: the class references many Groovy classes, so I have to define the real groovy.sql.Sql from source bytes or a jar. If my custom loader returns a custom-loaded Sql, its classloader will also be custom.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0163840d26182cc3016a2744155edc81978e0edb74ba56cb29\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJ0RPA0ikQhagJbreXxTvbVpfGxRT7mdZww5xkuG8dZowL3HsakO4XoiD3ehX7c68fb3AqbL9p6i8vhZMFtOvrWSLwImI6boynfK_Oi6-u6LIjA4qjiPhfDF9X-Qej_KKiiP5vn4n_4C9Nchc2pMnb5P_ir9QdTfbF4wU3SH1mODXz2vUxkCfWoXeFWPhPgG3XDIJV0CgKNsIbswb_ug1nkRh1mYu5Lqo4o8KX81G30VVT4Bh9plyDuHswD5PykxEvwWqeqoXJAclofa3sR2-X9sBTYXtCu6OGsLApuNmmgII8iRP7NvQ6O0idBVdwOG-cQcaRoo6WmplZXIckqoz2fIz5Lp_t_Ax6W7fvsoBzQrBQFPZdWzjJB6boEZXLCImFZeQlUbBM2ccxS5zaMZY6igx00JoDtPoOM4QF-fcm4bhYJhd48EzYWlklQmwqNZSykmREHnL88Z47Jv7l0NQ2wGL_jwe0PjomVqE8wkWQMHUNuAtUt1Gd2SiFQQOjQbPIX5yGcKkm-Xa_81fcpBX-0bAYHfjAwsikNn_aowbd0dGe2X2mAjPPKbxdtHHbQfHqHue4V5wJLLpq8_IkmpTXZDqCf-U2QoPfwXcreCvaGbEDxoURVDn7bHyxlMGRq907JXdPVGP6hmDTaegNl2nCjd1YK6DIs3sdSCCQu3Re1rsio8wVdwg75GIyW5ESsBS-rlIl2p-moxxxOkyiULLW06oRQiWCNHCSPZMkmAsaDSwqGyRBfnoI1eIBYnw2TOlwN6vm9QvDAPXW523N-9VB43Z9A2adCrg9SjWCq8pZFILTy3xQXkqR8TYkk6d1dXn7oe8FVp5f3Mh63Iow5oMeKsyS12xCQRLriQys1nKbsCZPAuCSCkigPmks4eF1cdpdlb3k6tkbt4EGzpJLiUHleUuqyBXMBMvjqITYAomJJ5YdfsWt71jHI5h68oxbWQ4QVXNSuo6HaC5398CGuXZF9UyiIqyXZ5W8j1lt_bmjuMqYZhvVz_rciu0ZkI0u9hkME8b9_H_hDgua7KXQEPjvVibfOR12xZmGTsjakEt8vUdHX4yZXkTjH-Kz-1cBMOh6H_xkzhLS0RqOzkFGBg6hI0WcC8PR1BtBIMgQbLLWoPJPnuIlCQj8bzxX2jXAi-FWJI4Y9IhqhtFyQgdyFBByDJHkNLettbfgBB-24zVUqsGQMj8nEzsQJA2-Gd5dj_I6fftSKXFjuapA5Wkl3tXeVocNqXkpd2gIwOAzqQ3dAwQ6YfXXpoYejCG3RhTIDxOByJPweTJcQC4EMaIeIU70MJIAWsj16yhjs_76Xadhm7DQVHhuNv0zAfghrnWrdAJJZaDuWgcvT