class, but I wonder if adding metadata for the VisibleDriver will be effective since it might get filtered out by user-code exclusions. Still, I think metadata shouldn't include test classes due to this filter. Let's move forward with the implementation!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering custom loader**\\n\\nI’m thinking about keeping the loader, but maybe a new custom loader would help trigger dynamic loading. I should ensure that the test file aligns perfectly. Also, I need to add imports for InvokerHelper and NativeImageSupport. I can use NativeImageSupport from the tck-test-support dependency that’s available. So, I’ll go ahead and make these edits. Time to get this working!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_RYno9vnAbU3cOohchPytSRaK|fc_0163840d26182cc3016a2744894cc88197a2072929de044bb5", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.codehaus.groovy/groovy-all/2.3.6/src/test/groovy/org_codehaus_groovy/groovy_all/SqlTest.groovy", "edits": [{"oldText": "import groovy.transform.CompileStatic\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test", "newText": "import groovy.transform.CompileStatic\nimport org.codehaus.groovy.runtime.InvokerHelper\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void reportsClassNotFoundWhenDriverCannotBeResolved() {", "newText": "    @Test\n    void loadsDriverClassFromSqlClassLoaderFallback() {\n        try {\n            ClassLoader originalContextClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader()\n            SqlFallbackClassLoader sqlLoader = new SqlFallbackClassLoader(\n                    Sql.class.getClassLoader(),\n                    readSqlClassBytes())\n            Class<?> isolatedSqlClass = sqlLoader.loadClass(Sql.name)\n\n            try {\n                Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(new RejectingClassLoader(\n                        originalContextClassLoader,\n                        VisibleDriver.name))\n                InvokerHelper.invokeStaticMethod(isolatedSqlClass, 'loadDriver', VisibleDriver.name)\n            } finally {\n                Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalContextClassLoader)\n            }\n\n            assertThat(sqlLoader.rejectedClassForNameAttempt).isTrue()\n            assertThat(sqlLoader.loadedDriverFromSqlLoaderFallback).isTrue()\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void reportsClassNotFoundWhenDriverCannotBeResolved() {"}, {"oldText": "    public static final class RejectingClassLoader extends ClassLoader {", "newText": "    private static byte[] readSqlClassBytes() throws IOException {\n        InputStream input = Sql.class.getResourceAsStream('Sql.class')\n        assertThat(input).isNotNull()\n        try {\n            return input.readAllBytes()\n        } finally {\n            input.close()\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class SqlFallbackClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private final byte[] sqlClassBytes\n        public boolean rejectedClassForNameAttempt\n        public boolean loadedDriverFromSqlLoaderFallback\n\n        SqlFallbackClassLoader(ClassLoader parent, byte[] sqlClassBytes) {\n            super(parent)\n            this.sqlClassBytes = sqlClassBytes\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        Class<?> loadClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (Sql.name == name) {\n                Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name)\n                if (loadedClass != null) {\n                    return loadedClass\n                }\n                return defineClass(name, sqlClassBytes, 0, sqlClassBytes.length)\n            }\n            if (VisibleDriver.name == name && !rejectedClassForNameAttempt) {\n                rejectedClassForNameAttempt = true\n                throw new ClassNotFoundException(name)